This paper deals with automatic sarcasm detection, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses domain adaptation, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
